   "SSExactMajority/LowerBound/Space.lean:4:0: * '\n# Space Lower Bound\n\nLemma 4: In a silent, safe configuration with |V_a| ≤ |V_b|,A-agents must have pairwise distinct states.\n\nKey idea: if two A-agents share state s_A, then δ((s_A,A),(s_A,A)) = (s_A,s_A)\nby silence. A population of n agents all in (s_A, A) is stuck outputting\nπ_out(s_A, A). SolvesSSEM forces this output to be A (majority = A),but in the original config the safe output is B or T. Contradiction.':\nIf an authors line spans multiple lines, each line but the last must end with a trailing comma\n\n\nNote: This linter can be disabled with `set_option linter.style.header false`",
